---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="B2B Web Design Chihuahua — Conversion-Focused Websites for Operations Companies | Facware"
  description="A website that doesn't convert is just an expense. Facware designs B2B web experiences built around your buyer's decision journey — fast load times, clear positioning, and a contact path that actually works."
  canonicalURL="https://facware.com/services/web-design.html"
  ogDescription="B2B web design for companies in Chihuahua and the US Southwest. Conversion-focused, built for your buyers, fast to load. Designed by Facware."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Service",
      "name": "B2B Web Design & Conversion Optimization",
      "description": "We design and build B2B websites for companies in Mexico and the US Southwest — focused on buyer decision journeys, performance, and lead generation, not aesthetics.",
      "provider": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Facware",
        "url": "https://facware.com"
      },
      "areaServed": ["Chihuahua, Mexico", "US Southwest"],
      "serviceType": "Web Design",
      "url": "https://facware.com/services/web-design.html"
    }
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <!-- PAGE HERO -->
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <i class="fas fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:10px"></i>
        <a href="/#facware_services">Services</a>
        <i class="fas fa-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:10px"></i>
        <span aria-current="page">Web Design &amp; Conversion</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>B2B Web Design Built Around Your Buyer's Decision Journey</h1>
      <p>Your website's job is to generate qualified conversations — not to win design awards. We build B2B web experiences with clear positioning, fast performance, and a contact path designed for buyers who are ready to move.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PROBLEM -->
  <section class="section" id="problem" aria-labelledby="problem-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">The B2B Website Problem</p>
        <h2 id="problem-heading">Most B2B websites are brochures — not sales assets</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">B2B buyers spend 6–8 hours researching a vendor before making contact. If your website doesn't answer the right questions in the right order, they leave — and contact your competitor instead.</p>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-3">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Positioning that doesn't speak to the buyer</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Your homepage says "we provide innovative solutions for your business." Your buyer has a specific problem and is looking for evidence that you've solved it before. Generic positioning creates no urgency and no confidence.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Slow load times that lose visitors before they read</h3>
          <p class="card-text">53% of B2B buyers abandon a site that takes more than 3 seconds to load. If your website scores below 60 on Core Web Vitals, you're losing qualified prospects — and ranking lower in search — because of technical issues, not content.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">A contact path that creates friction</h3>
          <p class="card-text">12-field contact forms. No indication of what happens next. A CTA that says "Contact Us" and links to a generic page. These are conversion killers that your visitors notice — and your analytics confirm, if anyone is looking.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DELIVERABLES -->
  <section class="section section--gray" id="deliverables" aria-labelledby="deliverables-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">What We Build</p>
        <h2 id="deliverables-heading">A website that earns its place in your sales process</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">Every web engagement we take on starts with your buyer — who they are, what they're evaluating, what objections they have — and works backward to the design and content.</p>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-2">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Positioning-led design</h3>
          <p class="card-text">We start with your differentiation, your buyer's decision criteria, and your competitive context — then design a homepage that speaks directly to the buyer you want to attract, not the buyer your competitors are already chasing.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Performance-first build</h3>
          <p class="card-text">We build on modern static frameworks (Astro) with lazy-loaded images, minimal JavaScript, and optimized assets. Pages load in under 2 seconds. Core Web Vitals scores in the green. SEO-ready from launch day.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Conversion-optimized contact flow</h3>
          <p class="card-text">We reduce contact form friction to the minimum required, set clear expectations for what happens next, and include multiple CTAs calibrated to different buyer readiness levels — from "just looking" to "ready to talk."</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">SEO foundation built in</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Unique page titles, meta descriptions, canonical URLs, structured data (JSON-LD), clean URL structure, and semantic HTML — the technical SEO foundation is built into every site we deliver, not bolted on afterward.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROCESS -->
  <section class="section" id="process" aria-labelledby="process-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">How It Works</p>
        <h2 id="process-heading">From buyer research to live website</h2>
      </header>
      <ol class="steps-grid" role="list">
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Website Assessment <span class="badge-free">(Free)</span></h3>
            <p>We audit your current site — Core Web Vitals, positioning clarity, conversion path, and SEO baseline. You get a clear picture of what's costing you leads, even if we never work together.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">02</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Positioning & Design</h3>
            <p>We clarify your positioning, map your buyer's decision journey, and design a site architecture that moves visitors from awareness to contact in the fewest steps. You review and approve the structure before any development begins.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <span class="step-num" aria-hidden="true">03</span>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3 class="step-title">Build, Launch & Optimize</h3>
            <p>We build the site, configure analytics, verify Core Web Vitals, and launch. Post-launch, we monitor conversion metrics and make data-driven adjustments through the 30-day stabilization period.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROOF METRICS -->
  <section class="section section--gray" aria-label="Web design results">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="results-grid">
        <div class="results-content">
          <p class="section-eyebrow">This site is an example</p>
          <h2>You're looking at our work right now.</h2>
          <ul class="results-list" role="list">
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Sub-2-second</strong> load times via Astro static build + Cloudflare CDN</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Green Core Web Vitals</strong> — LCP, CLS, and FID all within Google's recommended thresholds</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Buyer-first positioning</strong> — every headline addresses a specific pain, not a generic capability</span></li>
            <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span><span><strong>Conversion-ready contact flow</strong> — minimal friction, clear next step, multiple entry points</span></li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/contact.html#contact-form" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top:8px">Get a free website assessment &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="results-image">
          <img src="/assets/images/facware/resources_facware.png" alt="Web design results" loading="lazy" width="600" height="450">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RELATED SERVICES -->
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="related-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header text-center">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">Related Services</p>
        <h2 id="related-heading">A website is one part of the system</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="cards-grid cards-3">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/custom-software-development.html" class="link-primary">Custom Software Development</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">When your website needs to connect to internal systems — CRM, inventory, customer portals — we build both the front end and the integration layer as a single engagement.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/process-automation.html" class="link-primary">Process Automation</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">A high-converting website generates more leads. We can automate the intake process — lead routing, qualification emails, CRM entry — so no lead falls through the cracks.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title"><a href="/services/it-consulting.html" class="link-primary">IT Consulting</a></h3>
          <p class="card-text">If your website is one part of a larger technology problem, we start with an operations audit to make sure the web investment fits within the right overall strategy.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA BAND -->
  <section class="cta-band" aria-labelledby="cta-band-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 id="cta-band-heading">Find out what your website is costing you in lost leads</h2>
      <p>30-minute website assessment. We review your current site, score your conversion path, and tell you exactly what's driving prospects away — with no commitment required.</p>
      <a href="/contact.html#contact-form" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Book your free website assessment &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .cta-band {
    background: var(--primary);
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: clamp(56px, 8vw, 80px) 24px;
  }
  .cta-band h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .cta-band p {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 32px;
    opacity: 0.9;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
  .btn-lg {
    padding: 14px 36px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
</style>
